// Panels, spacers and splitters.

// Styles for panels:
//	Visual:
// 		LT_STYLE_PANEL_DOCUMENT - same background color as textbox - use to contain textual content
//		LT_STYLE_PANEL_FILLED - same background color as window - use to contain a page of controls
//		LT_STYLE_PANEL_INSET, LT_STYLE_PANEL_GROUP_BOX, LT_STYLE_PANEL_SHEET - use for grouping controls
//	Layout:
//		LT_STYLE_PANEL_FORM_TABLE - use for laying out controls in a table
//		LT_STYLE_PANEL_POPUP - use for laying out controls in a menu popup
//	Root level (the root panel/splitter should be one of these):
//		LT_STYLE_PANEL_WINDOW_DIVIDER - does not give the window a background color
//		LT_STYLE_PANEL_WINDOW_BACKGROUND - gives the window a background color, same as LT_STYLE_PANEL_FILLED
//		LT_STYLE_PANEL_WINDOW_WITH_STATUS_BAR_CONTENT - alternate version of LT_STYLE_PANEL_WINDOW_DIVIDER if the window has a status bar

